oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Whitehead family home in Cades Cove
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of a log and board house in Cades Cove. A barn can be seen in the background on the left. It is believed to belong to the Whitehead family. Henry Whitehead (1891-1914) was a carpenter and built the home for his wife Matilda "Tilda" Shields Whitehead (1842-1924), both pictured standing in front of the house.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:coverage: Great Smoky Mountains National Park (N.C. and Tenn.); Cades Cove (Tenn.); Sevier County (Tenn.)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Barns; Families; Houses
